Around the size of a rice bag, preferably larger ""I have never been a """"morning person"""". I wish waking up early was easy and enjoyable for me - the same way I wish I was inclined to like running or reading or olives or cold weather.
Getting out of bed remains one of my biggest struggles, and this past week I got into a cycle of going to bed around 4 or 5 am and getting out of bed around 2 pm. I needed to adjust my sleeping schedule so I didn't go to bed the previous night and went through yesterday in a bit of a daze. In a cafe that afternoon I sat down to a warm croissant and Earl Grey tea and spent about an hour watching random Ted talks on my phone and came across """" how waking up at 4:30 a.m. every day can change your life"""". The speaker was nervous and I found it difficult to sit through but I knew I wanted to hear his story. I concluded that I wasn't going to set lofty goals of waking up at 430 am, but I thought it would be really nice to wake up half an hour before the sunrise each morning so I can watch it and start my day that way. I checked the sunrise time in my weather app - 544 am - so I thought, """"get up at 515 am which means going to bed around 9 pm to have enough sleep .. hmm that won't work, but I'll still aim for a reasonably early time to get up.""""
Woke up at 6:40 am today =)"" I grew up in Vancouver, lived here my entire life - almost 30 years. Never quite settled in though, always dreamt of something more, and travelled as much as I could to find my place in the world and to feel like I belong. But it's time for me to be happy where I am and with who I am. For the first time, I'm going to try and make Vancouver my home  I miss your dog!! (and you too, of course) Passed my exam!!
